      <title>Useful linux commands</title>
      <link>https://stefanosgeo.github.io/snippets/my-first-post/</link>
      <pubDate>Fri, 21 Mar 2025 22:42:54 +0100</pubDate>
      <guid>https://stefanosgeo.github.io/snippets/my-first-post/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;These are some useful commands that I use for everday working with linux&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;lists folders size inside a folder: &lt;code&gt;du -hs .[^.]* * | sort -h &lt;/code&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Connect to keychron keyboard using chrome in linux: &lt;code&gt;sudo chmod a+rw /dev/hidraw3&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;</description>
